    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the goblin confusion, I hope that didn't cause too much of a stir! Regarding the airport chaos, it's understandable that the situation can feel overwhelming. In addition to keeping an eye on flight times, there are a few other things you should be aware of:\n\n1. Security Checkpoints: Be prepared for longer wait times at security checkpoints, especially during peak travel times. Make sure you have all your travel documents readily accessible to speed up the process.\n\n2. Baggage Claim: If you're traveling with checked luggage, keep an eye on the baggage claim area. It's easy to get lost in the crowd, so try to stay near the area where your flight is departing.\n\n3. Transportation: Once you board your flight, be aware of the airport's transportation options. Some airports have shuttle services or trains that can help you get to your gate more quickly.\n\n4. Communication: Keep your phone charged and have a portable charger handy. It's important to stay connected and be able to communicate with your airline or fellow travelers if needed.\n\n5. Restroom Breaks: If you need to use the restroom, try to find a quiet area away from the main crowds. It's always good to be prepared and avoid any unnecessary stress.\n\nRemember,",
